  "id": "019d286a-f2d8-78b2-92cd-448d2a289f6f",
  "content": "### Step 4: Implement LiteStore struct and constructor\n\n    db: Database,\n    hnsw: Arc<Mutex<Hnsw<f32, DistCosine>>>,\n    next_hnsw_id: AtomicU64,\n    dimensions: usize,\n}\n```\n\n**Note on hnsw_rs API:** The exact type signatures for `Hnsw`, `insert`, `search`, and `Neighbour` fields are based on docs research. If compile errors occur:\n- `Hnsw::new()` takes `(max_nb_connection, max_elements, nb_layer, ef_construction, DistCosine{})`\n- `hnsw.insert()` takes a tuple of `(&Vec<f32>, usize)` — the data and an ID\n- `hnsw.search()` returns `Vec<Neighbour>` — check field names: likely `d_id` (usize) and `distance` (f32)\n- If `Hnsw` requires lifetime parameter (`Hnsw<'a, f32, DistCosine>`), use `'static` or restructure with owned data\n\nConstructor and helpers:\n\n```rust\nimpl LiteStore {\n    pub fn open(data_dir: &Path, dimensions: usize) -> Result<Self> {\n        std::fs::create_dir_all(data_dir)\n            .map_err(|e| CorviaError::Storage(format!(\"Failed to create data dir: {e}\")))?;\n\n        let db_path = data_dir.join(\"metadata.redb\");\n        let db = Database::create(&db_path)\n            .map_err(|e| CorviaError::Storage(format!(\"Failed to open Redb: {e}\")))?;",
